description.p:
 an amino acid with a chemically similar amino acid. Conservative substitution tables providing functionally similar amino acids are well known in the art. The following six groups each contain amino acids that are conservative substitutions for one another: 
1) Alanine (A), Serine (S), Threonine (T); 
2) Aspartic acid (D), Glutamic acid (E); 
3) Asparagine (N), Glutamine (Q) ; 
4) Arginin (R), Lysine (K); 
5) Isoleucine (I), Leucine (L), Methionine (M), Valine (V); and 
6) Phenylalanine (F), Tyrosine (Y), Tryptophan (W).
